parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight adjuster can cause poor visibility while driving at night, leading to a significant safety hazard, as the driver may not be able to see the road ahead, increasing the risk of accidents or pedestrian fatalities.
symptoms: The headlights are not high enough to shine on the road
only illuminating 15-20 feet in front of the vehicle
or the headlights point downwards
reducing visibility to 25 feet or less.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of the airbag can cause physical harm to the driver and passengers, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without a crash or impact
causing injury to the driver or passengers
often accompanied by a loud noise and a cloud of powder.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag in the steering wheel can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to physical harm to the driver and potentially causing accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without a crash or impact
causing injury to the driver
often accompanied by a loud noise and a cloud of powder.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cooling System Failure and Head Gasket Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to head gasket failure, engine damage, and potentially catastrophic consequences. This can result in costly repairs, vehicle downtime, and safety risks.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
engine overheating
head gasket failure
temperature gauge not registering overheating conditions
coolant system emptying without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to a loss of control, increased stopping distance, or even accidents, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels to the floor
inability to stop the vehicle
extended stopping distance
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
brake warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shock support can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The shock support comes completely out of the body of the vehicle
unusual noises or vibrations while driving
loss of vehicle stability
uneven tire wear.
